cs.NE, cs.BI, cs.ET, cs.RO, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of Physarum polycephalum, a biological organism, for computation and chemical sensing. This falls under the category of bio-inspired and neuromorphic computing, which is covered by cs.NE. The paper also discusses the use of electrical potential recordings and sensory fusion, which could fall under the categories of biological physics (cs.BI) and embedded systems (cs.ET). The use of the organism for robotics and control is also mentioned, which could fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
